3ECheyenne%20Board%20of%20Public%20Utilities%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMeta%20is%20building%20a%20715%2C000-square-foot%20data%20center%20campus%20in%20Cheyenne%2C%20Wyoming.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20city%20said%20the%20project%20is%20responsible%20for%20contaminating%20part%20of%20its%20recycled%20water%20system%2C%20used%20only%20for%20irrigation%20purposes.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMeta%20is%20working%20with%20its%20contractor%20to%20resolve%20the%20issue.%20The%20city%20stopped%20accepting%20industrial%20wastewater%20from%20all%20data%20centers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOfficials%20in%20the%20city%20of%20Cheyenne%2C%20Wyoming%2C%20say%20a%20massive%2C%20under-construction%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-ruthless-management-style-reckoning-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMeta%3C%2Fa%3E%20data%20center%20campus%20located%20just%20south%20of%20the%20city%20is%20responsible%20for%20contaminating%20part%20of%20its%20recycled%20water%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECheyenne's%20Board%20of%20Public%20Utilities%20said%20in%20recent%20public%20notices%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethat%20water%20discharged%20by%20Goat%20Systems%2C%20a%20Meta%20contractor%20at%20the%20site%3Cem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Econtaminated%20the%20city's%20wastewater%20treatment%20facility%20with%20a%20rare%20bacterium.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20facility%20includes%20Cheyenne's%20reuse%20water%20system%2C%20which%20is%20used%20for%20irrigation%20purposes%20only%2C%20a%20board%20spokesperson%20said.%20The%20system%20cleans%20used%20water%20so%20it%20can%20be%20safely%20released%20back%20into%20the%20environment%20or%20reused%20for%20watering%20things%20like%20parks%20and%20golf%20courses.%20The%20bacterium%20did%20not%20enter%20the%20city's%20drinking%20supply%2C%20city%20officials%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20able%20to%20connect%20the%20Meta%20Data%20Center%20campus%20to%20this%20through%20sampling%20their%20site%20and%20it%20was%20determined%20to%20be%20through%20their%20fill-and-flush%20discharge%20that%20the%20bacteria%20was%20introduced%20to%20the%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20Erin%20Lamb%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20Board%20of%20Public%20Utilities%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFill-and-flush%20operations%20are%20a%20cooling%20system%20for%20data%20centers%20in%20which%20water%20is%20periodically%20flushed%20from%20pipes%2C%20discarded%2C%20and%20then%20replenished%20with%20new%20water.%20Some%20data%20centers%20now%20use%20a%20%26quot%3Bclosed-loop%26quot%3B%20system%20that%20recycles%20the%20same%20water%20within%20the%20facility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20board's%20public%20notice%20characterized%20the%20infraction%20as%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20noncompliance%26quot%3B%20and%20revoked%20Goat%20Systems'%20%26quot%3Bindustrial%20discharge%20privileges%20for%20fill%20and%20flush%20operations.%26quot%3B%20While%20the%20board%20posted%20the%20notice%20on%20July%202%2C%20it%20said%20the%20operations%20were%20halted%20on%20March%2024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoat%20Systems%2C%20the%20Meta%20contractor%2C%20%26quot%3Bimmediately%20ceased%20discharge%20of%20wastewater%20from%20the%20fill%20and%20flush%20operation%26quot%3B%20after%20it%20was%20notified%20of%20the%20pollutant%2C%20Cheyenne's%20Board%20of%20Public%20Utilities%20said.%20A%20representative%20for%20Goat%20Systems%20could%20not%20be%20reached%20for%20comment%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Meta%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20company%20is%20working%20with%20its%20general%20contractor%2C%20Fortis%2C%20to%20resolve%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20board%20shared%20that%20it%20found%20a%20substance%20in%20the%20city's%20wastewater%20%E2%80%94%20not%20public%20drinking%20water%20%E2%80%94%20Fortis%20immediately%20stopped%20discharging%20industrial%20wastewater%20and%20began%20hauling%20it%20offsite%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%20%26quot%3BFortis%20also%20began%20its%20own%20water%20testing%20with%20an%20independent%20environmental%20specialist%2C%20which%20has%20found%20no%20trace%20of%20the%20substance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Fortis%20said%20the%20company%20%26quot%3Btakes%20its%20environmental%20obligations%20seriously%20and%20will%20continue%20to%20work%20constructively%20with%20BOPU%20and%20all%20relevant%20authorities%20as%20this%20matter%20is%20fully%20resolved.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Cheyenne%20Board%20of%20Public%20Utilities%20said%20in%20its%20notice%20that%20it%20would%20pause%20accepting%20any%20industrial%20water%20discharge%20from%20any%20data%20center%2C%20whether%20it's%20a%20fill-and-flush%20or%20closed-loop%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fplugins%2Fpost.php%3Fhref%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.facebook.com%252Fcheyennebopu%252Fposts%252Fpfbid037P9Fk2iK6Pr39qwMRzodN7rweC1QVYy7tttQM2MwYYKdmTkrYJJZMH8L7cZr9HAAl%26show_text%3Dtrue%26width%3D500%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22566%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20board%20said%20the%20bacterium%20it%20found%20in%20the%20wastewater%20was%20Cupriavidus%20gilardii.%20Although%20infections%20are%20rare%2C%20direct%20exposure%20can%20pose%20a%20risk%20to%20older%20people%20or%20those%20who%20are%20immunocompromised.%20Laboratory%20staff%20identified%20the%20bacterium%20during%20a%20wastewater%20sampling%20in%20February%2C%20the%20board%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOver%20the%20past%20two%20months%2C%20BOPU%20staff%20have%20undertaken%20significant%20remediation%20efforts%2C%20including%20draining%20and%20disinfecting%20the%20entire%20reuse%20water%20system%20and%20Prairie%20View%20Pond%20to%20eliminate%20any%20remaining%20bacterial%20presence%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20board%20said%20in%20its%20notice.%20%26quot%3BTo%20prevent%20potential%20migration%20throughout%20the%20reuse%20distribution%20network%2C%20all%20affected%20irrigation%20systems%20were%20temporarily%20converted%20to%20potable%20water%20supplies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELamb%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20for%20BOPU%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20agency%20plans%20to%20hold%20a%20press%20conference%20on%20the%20matter%20in%20the%20next%20week%20or%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20announced%20the%20%24800%20million%2C%20715%2C000-square-foot%20data%20center%20development%20in%202024.%20Once%20the%20campus%20is%20fully%20operational%2C%20Meta%20says%20it%20will%20be%20wholly%20sustainable.%20The%20company%20said%20it%20aims%20to%20be%20water-positive%20by%202030%2C%20meaning%20it%20will%20restore%20more%20water%20than%20it%20consumes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Cheyenne%20Data%20Center%20will%20be%20optimized%20for%20our%20AI%20workloads%20and%20help%20people%20connect%2C%20build%20communities%2C%20and%20grow%20their%20businesses%2C%26quot%3B%20Meta%20said%20at%20the%20time%20of%20its%20announcement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20centers%20have%20become%20a%20divisive%20topic.%20Tech%20companies%20are%20spending%20billions%20of%20dollars%20to%20develop%20the%20facilities%20that%20power%20their%20AI%20products.%20They%20say%20data%20centers%20can%20generate%20economic%20growth%2C%20create%20jobs%2C%20and%20push%20the%20US%20ahead%20in%20the%20AI%20race%20against%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECritics%2C%20however%2C%20are%20much%20less%20enthused.%20Many%20Americans%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frural-towns-ai-data-centers-resistance-personal-finance-electricity-bills-2026-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epushing%20back%20against%20data%20centers%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20don't%20want%20them%20anywhere%20near%20their%20communities.%20They're%20concerned%20that%20the%20sprawling%20facilities%20will%20negatively%20impact%20water%20resources%2C%20worsen%20air%20quality%2C%20increase%20noise%20levels%2C%20and%20interfere%20with%20their%20quality%20of%20life.%20Some%20protesters%20have%20swarmed%20local%20planning%20meetings%2C%20created%20petitions%2C%20and%20taken%20legal%20action%20to%20stop%20construction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20a%20handful%20of%20legislators%20have%20taken%20steps%20to%20place%20parameters%20around%20data%20center%20developments%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-center-bans-moratoriums-opposition-map-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eban%20them%3C%2Fa%3E%20altogether.%20At%20the%20federal%20level%2C%20Sens.%20Bernie%20Sanders%20of%20Vermont%20and%20Alexandria%20Ocasio-Cortez%20of%20New%20York%20proposed%20a%20moratorium%20on%20AI%20data%20centers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-data-center-boom-is-colliding-with-the-midterms-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edata%20center%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20still%20speeding%20full%20steam%20ahead%2C%20however.%20By%20the%20end%20of%202025%2C%20there%20were%20over%201%2C400%20data%20centers%20built%20or%20approved%20for%20construction%20in%2045%20states%20and%20Washington%2C%20DC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-data-center-waste-water-bacterium-cheyenne-wyoming-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783458942000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4d58ff965805a2c542dc90%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-data-center-waste-water-bacterium-cheyenne-wyoming-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Officials%20in%20Cheyenne%2C%20Wyoming%2C%20say%20a%20nearby%20Meta%20data%20center%20campus%20is%20responsible%20for%20contaminating%20part%20of%20its%20water%20recycling%20irrigation%20system.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ledmonds%40bus