%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESreeja%20Apparaju%20is%20a%20machine%20learning%20engineer%20at%20Snap.%20She's%20in%20her%2020s%20and%20lives%20in%20New%20York.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20misconception%20is%20that%20tech%20jobs%20are%20all%20hoodies%2C%20ping%20pong%20tables%2C%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkers-try-four-day-workweek-burnout-mental-health-research-productivity-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efour-hour%20workday%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20perks%20are%20real%2C%20but%20they%20exist%20alongside%20the%20genuine%20intensity%20of%20on-call%20rotations%2C%20launch%20crunches%2C%20performance%20reviews%2C%20and%20the%20constant%20pressure%20to%20keep%20learning%20as%20the%20stack%20evolves%20under%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20the%20assumption%20that%20the%20work%20is%20purely%20solitary%20and%20screen-bound.%20The%20technical%20problems%20are%20only%20half%20of%20it%3B%20the%20other%20half%20is%20people%3A%20understanding%20what%20users%20actually%20need%2C%20negotiating%20priorities%20with%20partners%2C%20and%20communicating%20clearly%20enough%20that%20the%20right%20decisions%20get%20made%20even%20when%20you're%20not%20in%20the%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20is%20speaking%20with%20tech%20workers%20who've%20found%20themselves%20at%20a%20corporate%20crossroads%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20due%20to%20a%20layoff%2C%20resignation%2C%20job%20search%2C%20or%20shifting%20workplace%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShare%20your%20story%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSechTVqVWQve8iqYssNriCXdtwwdgGRixNNZpmslSKBQqIJ8g%2Fviewform%3Fusp%3Dheader%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efilling%20out%20this%20form%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2245d5d01c-2efe-4baf-b58a-418a0474cc68%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAI%20can't%20do%20your%20thinking%20for%20you%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221119%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Udit%20Mehrotra%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4bfc3494175b768171f4ee%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22839%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUdit%20Mehrotra%20says%20AI%20can't%20replace%20critical%20thinking.%3Cp%3EUdit%20Mehrotra%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUdit%20Mehrotra%20is%20a%20head%20of%20product%20at%20Amazon.%20He's%20in%20his%2030s%20and%20lives%20in%20Seattle.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20misconception%20I%20come%20across%20right%20now%20is%20that%20you%20can%20outsource%20your%20thinking%20to%20AI.%20A%20lot%20of%20people%20have%20discovered%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-tools-doubled-income-save-me-fifteen-hours-each-week-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20tools%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20genuinely%20impressive%20at%20producing%20output%20quickly%2C%20and%20the%20temptation%20is%20to%20let%20the%20tools%20drive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20is%20that%20the%20quality%20of%20what%20comes%20out%20is%20almost%20entirely%20determined%20by%20the%20quality%20of%20thinking%20you%20put%20in.%20Garbage%20in%2C%20garbage%20out%2C%20except%20now%20it's%20faster%20and%20looks%20more%20polished.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221d1c7a9d-f7ad-4d18-8b12-195436e1ee8b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20bar%20keeps%20getting%20higher%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mike%20Kostersitz%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4bfe905dc133dbf310d4fd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMike%20Kostersitz%20says%20AI%20hasn't%20made%20his%20job%20easier.%3Cp%3EMike%20Kostersitz%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMike%20Kostersitz%20is%20a%20senior%20director%2C%20product%20management%20at%20Nike.%20He's%2060%20and%20lives%20in%20Oregon.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20common%20misconception%20is%20that%20tech%20workers%20are%20coasting%20%E2%80%94%20making%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20for%20very%20little%20work%20because%20AI%20does%20the%20rest.%20That%20gets%20it%20backwards.%20AI%20doesn't%20hand%20you%20free%20time%3B%20it%20removes%20the%20repetitive%20work%20that%20used%20to%20crowd%20out%20the%20important%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20job%20hasn't%20gotten%20easier%20%E2%80%94%20the%20bar%20has%20gotten%20higher.%20We're%20expected%20to%20think%20more%20clearly%2C%20decide%20faster%2C%20and%20lead%20through%20more%20change%20in%20a%20quarter%20than%20we%20used%20to%20in%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ac5a4fb0-5b7f-4396-9684-dc62009786a4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETech%20is%20much%20bigger%20than%20software%20engineering%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221119%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Prerit%20Pathak%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4bfef194175b768171f502%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22839%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPrerit%20Pathak%20says%20working%20in%20tech%20is%20about%20much%20more%20than%20software%20engineering.%3Cp%3EPrerit%20Pathak%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPrerit%20Pathak%20is%20a%20security%20engineer%20at%20Google.%20He's%20in%20his%2020s%20and%20lives%20in%20New%20York%20City.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20many%20people%20mistakenly%20believe%20that%20being%20a%20%26quot%3Btech%20employee%26quot%3B%20is%20synonymous%20with%20being%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoftware-engineer-developer-ai-coding-views-2026-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esoftware%20engineer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20reality%20is%20that%20technology%20is%20a%20vast%20ecosystem%20of%20roles%20like%20Product%20Management%2C%20UI%2FUX%20Design%2C%20Data%20Science%2C%20and%20Cybersecurity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20specialists%20act%20as%20the%20architects%2C%20maintainers%2C%20and%20protectors%20of%20the%20digi